    <h1>Real Cost of UNL</h1>

<img class="img-responsive" src="nebraska.jpg" alt="Nebraska Logo">
    <p>The University of Nebraska-Lincoln has a lot to offer, but is it really worth the cost?</p>
    <p>The University of Nebraska-Lincoln is the state's oldest and largest university chartered in 1869,<a href="_historic.html"> over the years</a> it has expanded to a total enrollment of 25,260 students as of 2015 and has many top-rated programs.</p> 
   <p>The University of Nebraska-Liincoln is a member of the <a href="_bigten.html">Big Ten Conference</a> which is the oldest Division 1 collegiate athletic conference in the USA. Big Ten member institutions are predominatly major flagship research universities that have large financial endowments and are well-regarded academically.</p>
<p> As of fall 2015, UNL was among the top 50 public universities listed in U.S. News and World Report's annual evaluation of America's Best Colleges. Princeton Review and Kiplinger's listed it as a best value public university in 2014 and The National Jurist listed it as #1 Best Value Law School in the U.S. as of 2015. Read more about enrollment <a href="_statistics.html">statistics</a>.</p>


